IN HOST MACHINE (assume 192.168.100.101)
1. modify and run ./_init/full_selfsign/generate-cert.sh
2. create a _init/full_selfsign/hosts to point all subdomains to 192.168.100.101 and localhost to 127.0.0.1 if necessary
3. config reverse_proxy.conf to self signed cert.

IN USER MACHINE (assume 192.168.100.200)
1. update /etc/hosts to point all subdomains to 192.168.100.101
2. update firefox config
3. import RootCA.crt into firefox via about:preferences#privacy => View certificates => import => check `Trust this CA to identity websites`
4. visit via url